entry.name: Multi-omic analysis of Yersinia response to temperature shift
entry.description: A temporal multi-omic analysis of Y. pestis and Y. pseudotuberculosis at physiologically relevant temperatures was performed to gain insights into how an acute and highly lethal bacterial pathogen, Y. pestis, differs from its less virulent progenitor, Y. pseudotuberculosis. Associated transcriptomics data have been deposited in GEO under accession number GSE30634.

additional_fields.field: Schrimpe-Rutledge AC, Jones MB, Chauhan S, Purvine SO, Sanford JA, Monroe ME, Brewer HM, Payne SH, Ansong C, Frank BC, Smith RD, Peterson SN, Motin VL, Adkins JN; Comparative omics-driven genome annotation refinement: application across Yersiniae., PLoS One, 2012, 7, 3, e33903,
